Release manual

Note: if the .htaccess file is accidentally deleted from the server it can be copy-pasted from this repository.


Begin with:
* Make sure that all changed are commited and pushed
* yarn test

Labb (always use dev-branch):
* yarn build
* rsync --delete --exclude ".htaccess" -r dist/ fkkorp@k2.spraakdata.gu.se:/var/www/html_sb/korplabb (deploy)

Release candidate
  - on dev: bump the version number in packages.json and app/markup/about.html
  - on master: merge dev
  - on master:
      > yarn build
      > rsync --delete --exclude ".htaccess" -r dist/ fkkorp@demo.spraakdata.gu.se:/export/htdocs/korprc (deploy)

    Available at: http://demo.spraakdata.gu.se/korprc/

Production:

  Skip first two steps for config-changes

  On master:
    > tag latest release
    > run release.sh and upload zip to web
    > yarn build
    > rsync --delete --exclude ".htaccess" -r dist/ fkkorp@k2.spraakdata.gu.se:/var/www/html_sb/korp (deploy)

